  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is an inclusive education pilot that supports 9,000 war-affected school children aged 6 to 16 years to benefit from a more inclusive and improved quality learning environment in turn improving their school retention and academic performance. To achieve this the project trains teachers in inclusive education and accelerated learning training; deploys a Learning Support Assistant Scheme to give individual support to children with learning disabilities; gives grants to families to ensure long term commitment and financial capacities to support children&#x2019;s schooling.</narrative>
